B \subseteq \mathbb R
\mathscr X_B: \mathbb R \rightarrow \mathbb R 
B
\mathscr X_B(x)=1
x \in B
\mathscr X_B(x)=0
x \notin B
\mathscr X_B
B
\mathscr X_B(x)
x_b \in \mathbb R
\Rightarrow \forall \varepsilon > 0, \exists \delta >0
x \in \mathbb R, |x-x_b|< \delta \rightarrow \mathscr X_B (x) > \mathscr X_B(x_b) - \varepsilon
x_b \in B
\Rightarrow
\mathscr X_B(x_b) = 1
x \in B
\mathscr X_B(x) = 1
1=1- \varepsilon
